This paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves designing algorithms that can implement fair allocation, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the economic implications of fair allocation, which is related to computational economics (cs.EC) and decision making (cs.DS).
